The State Election Board takes no position on the propriety or value of a party’s decision to request a subpoena as it is not involved in the substantive issues until it hears the cause for which subpoenas were requested. (3)
The party or party’s attorney is responsible for deciding which witnesses to call & documents or other pieces of evidence to request in support of the allegations raised. (2)

Q: I requested an absentee ballot. Can I vote in person instead?
A: Only if you swear affidavit that you did not vote your absentee ballot.

Q: Can I write in the name of a candidate?
A: No. OK law doesn't allow write-in candidates, but writing does not invalidate rest of ballot.

Q: Does leaving a race blank invalidate my ballot?
A: No. If you leave a race blank (aka undervote), your votes in other races still count.
